Mohai first served in Parliament in 1999 as a Member of Parliament. CAPE TOWN - The National Council of Provinces (NCOP) has unanimously elected Seiso Mohai as its new chief whip.This follows the resignation of Hunadi Mateme as announced by NCOP chairperson Thandi Modise on Thursday afternoon. Before I proceed, I would like to announce that I have received a letter of resignation from the honourable Dr HE Mateme as chief whip of council. Mateme had served since the 2014 general elections.Mohai first served in Parliament in 1999 as a Member of Parliament, but was redeployed by the African National Congress in 2001 to serve in the Free State in various capacities including as an MEC, before returning to Parliament in 2009.